    "details": {
      "blurb": "THE QUEEN — two souls, one crown (B20)",
      "languages": {
        "details": "",
        "value": [
          "common",
          "infernal",
          "thassilonian",
          "varisian",
          "shadowtongue"
        ]
      },
      "level": {
        "value": 21
      },
      "privateNotes": "",
      "publicNotes": "<p><strong>THE FINAL BOSS (B20, the Everdawn Pool).</strong> Two souls wear one crown: the spoiled queen, and the seed of <strong>Kazavon</strong> ripening inside her. She floats in trance at the Pool's heart — <strong>10 days remain</strong> on the ritual (give the party two attempts; driven off twice, she finishes it — see What If Ileosa Wins). Noticing intruders, she releases the six @UUID[Compendium.cotct-pf2e-conversion.cotct-actors.Actor.falseIleosa00001]{false Ileosas}, her @UUID[Compendium.cotct-pf2e-conversion.cotct-actors.Actor.ileosasFury00001]{Furies} teleport in, @UUID[Compendium.cotct-pf2e-conversion.cotct-actors.Actor.ithierGylou00001]{Ithier} climbs from below — and the Pool spins up a @UUID[Compendium.cotct-pf2e-conversion.cotct-actors.Actor.taniniverKaz0001]{taniniver} (5 charges each, replaceable). <strong>Only Serithtial ends her</strong>: suppress the regeneration, sunder the Crown, and the dragon-soul dies screaming. Her contract: un-raiseable without @UUID[Compendium.cotct-pf2e-conversion.cotct-actors.Actor.sermignattoDvl01]{Sermignatto's} leave; his master Lorthact inherits if he's dead.</p>",
      "publication": {
        "title": "Pathfinder: Curse of the Crimson Throne (PF2e conversion, private)",
        "authors": "",
        "license": "OGL",
        "remaster": true
      }
